## Why This Case Is a Good Demo

This case is useful for a radiology-reasoning demo because the vascular anatomy is visually complex. RSNA’s Top Images in Radiology commentary notes that the axial images are striking but may not make the vascular pathway easy to trace, while cinematic rendering helps depict the unusual coronary artery–left atrial fistula and supports final interpretation.

That is exactly the kind of scenario where a structured reasoning scaffold can help: not by replacing the radiologist, but by forcing the analysis to separate visible evidence, suspected vessel relationships, certainty level, and needed confirmation.

In this demo, ClarityWise recognized the image as coronary CTA, identified a complex vascular coronary abnormality, connected it to RCA and LCX territories, favored a fistula/vascular-malformation category, and preserved uncertainty around the drainage site until the caption was supplied.

